.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple command line interpreter.

It displays a prompt in interactive mode, reads one command per line,
creates a child process with
.BR fork (2),
executes the command with
.BR execve (2),
and waits for the command to finish.

This version supports only one-word commands given as absolute paths.

It also works in non-interactive mode, for example when input is piped
from another command or from a file.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
Prompt
Displays
.B ($)
when standard input is a terminal.
.TP
Command execution
Executes one command at a time using
.BR execve (2).
.TP
Process handling
Creates a child process and waits for it with
.BR wait (2).
.TP
End of file
Exits cleanly on
.B Ctrl+D
in interactive mode.

.SH LIMITATIONS
This version does not:
.TP
Use PATH
Commands must be written as absolute paths.
.TP
Handle arguments
Only one-word commands are supported.
.TP
Implement built-ins
Commands such as
.B exit
and
.B env
are not built in.
.TP
Handle advanced shell syntax
No pipes, redirections, semicolons, quotes, or wildcards.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on normal exit.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
main.c execute.c main.h README.md
($)
.fi

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
main.c execute.c main.h README.md
.fi

